What you should worry about is taking care of yourself so that your mom won't be worried.

83
00:06:28,830 --> 00:06:34,160
When your grandma is healed, you will be able to meet her in a good condition.

84
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,690
How wonderful would that be?

85
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:39,660
Don't worry.

86
00:06:39,660 --> 00:06:42,130
Your grandma will be fine.

87
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:45,779
Finish your food.

88
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:59,290
Auntie, I'd like to head back now.

89
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:04,300
Xianxian, stay here for a little longer.

90
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,497
It's okay, Auntie.

91
00:07:05,497 --> 00:07:07,170
I've been staying here for a day now.

92
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:09,490
I've bothered you enough.

93
00:07:09,490 --> 00:07:12,060
Pay more attention now that you are living by yourself.

94
00:07:12,060 --> 00:07:14,970
Tell me if anything happens.

95
00:07:14,970 --> 00:07:17,600
- Siyue, go walk Xianxian home.
 - All right.

96
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:21,660
It's okay. My place is really close. I can walk out on my own.

97
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:22,820
Okay.

98
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:24,540
Be careful on your way home.

99
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:26,180
- Don't worry, Auntie.
 - All right.

100
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:28,060
- See you, Auntie.
 - See you.

101
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:29,860
Take care.

102
00:07:35,513 --> 00:07:39,366
It would be great if my parents allowed you to stay at my place.

103
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:41,750
It's okay.

104
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:45,110
It's the same to talk to me on the phone at night.

105
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:47,970
 Aren't you afraid to stay at home by yourself?

106
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:50,033
 And what if...

107
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,450
Stop that. I didn't think this would matter.

108
00:07:52,450 --> 00:07:54,940
But now that you've said it, I feel...

109
