Shadi!

110
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:09,900
Stop talking for a second.

111
00:09:33,610 --> 00:09:36,780
Get out. Someone is here, in the apartment. Go!

112
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:38,780
It's me.

113
00:09:42,220 --> 00:09:44,790
That's some heavy strikes.

114
00:09:45,540 --> 00:09:46,910
You...

115
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:49,050
How did you...

116
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:52,860
Your mom left a spare key in our place before she left.

117
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:55,500
I've been knocking forever but no one answered.

118
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,820
I was afraid.

119
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:58,820
I thought you were...

120
00:09:58,820 --> 00:10:00,620
I'm just glad that everything is fine.

121
00:10:00,620 --> 00:10:03,959
The security guard caught a thief scouting the area.

122
00:10:03,959 --> 00:10:05,945
A thief?

123
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:09,130
Look at your door.

124
00:10:09,130 --> 00:10:11,320
It's marked.

125
00:10:19,053 --> 00:10:20,653
Hello?

126
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:23,660
She's fine. She's with me.

127
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:25,762
You guys go home now.

128
00:10:27,610 --> 00:10:29,540
Who is that?

129
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:31,026
It's Song Ziqi.

130
00:10:31,026 --> 00:10:33,930
Kong Shadi told him that you were in danger.

131
00:10:33,930 --> 00:10:36,050
They were on their way here.

132
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,200
You scared the hell out of me.

133
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:47,540
It must be really troublesome for you.

134
00:10:47,540 --> 00:10:49,180
How could that be troublesome?

135
00:10:49,180 --> 00:10:51,780
You are acting like a stranger right now.

136
00:10:52,460 --> 00:10:54,906
Thank you for taking care of Xianxian.

137
00:10:54,906 --> 00:10:58,136
I'll be right on my way once things are done over here.

138
00:10:58,136 --> 00:10:59,900
Keep in touch.

139
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,340
All right. See you.

140
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,370
Here.

141
00:11:10,553 --> 00:11:11,962
Auntie,

142
00:11:11,962 --> 00:11:14,900
I might be bothering you for a while.

143
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:19,160
Don't say that. You are always too polite.

144
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,050
I'm glad that you are fine.

145
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:24,380
I can still sense the terror.

146
00:11:24,380 --> 00:11:26,980
We told you to stay with us.

147
00:11:28,180 --> 00:11:33,890
Oh, Siyue. Go help Xianxian pack her things and move here as soon as possible.

148
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:38,120
It's okay. I can pack my things on my own.

149
00:11:41,810 --> 00:11:44,950
I'm glad that Xianxian is fine, and nothing really happened.

150
00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:46,200
What did I tell you?

151
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,860
They live so closely. If anything happens,

152
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:51,066
Siyue will rush to her place right away.

153
00:11:51,066 --> 00:11:53,050
I was worried about her.

154
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:55,930
Do you think everyone is careless like you are?

155
00:11:55,930 --> 00:11:57,890
Fortunately, Siyue is considerate.

156
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:01,820
If anything happens to me, would you be there?

157
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:03,610
Have some conscience!

158
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:07,559
Have I ever been absent when anything happens to you?

159
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:11,880
Maybe not.

160
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,780
You should pay more attention to my good deeds.

161
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:15,670
You've done more bad things.

162
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:18,110
How am I supposed to remember all those things?

163
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:19,740
This is boring. Let's go.

164
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,940
Where are we going?

165
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:23,658
We are already out. It's still early.

166
00:12:23,658 --> 00:12:25,360
You can't be considering going home.

167
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,117
There's a restaurant over there.

168
00:12:27,117 --> 00:12:29,217
I'll take you for a meal.

169
00:12:29,217 --> 00:12:31,525
Never mind. I should pay for it.

170
00:12:33,370 --> 00:12:35,010
You are treating me to a meal?

171
00:12:35,010 --> 00:12:36,250
Am I hallucinating?

172
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:38,050
What?

173
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:44,750
Since you've taken a lot of bullets for me, this one is on me. Let's go.

174
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:47,080
Thank you, Shadi.

175
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:57,700

176
00:12:57,700 --> 00:13:03,130

177
00:13:20,340 --> 00:13:21,960

178
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,800

